jnxWxMibModule.name: jnxWxMibModule

revisions.description: o Add compression and throughput statistics to the jnxWxSysStats group. o Add bytes counts to jnxWxAsmStatsTable. o Add bytes counts and bytes-in percentage to jnxWxAppStatsTable. o Add jnxWxAppAggrStatsTable.
Rev 1.0 Initial version of MIB module JUNIPER-WX-MIB.

jnxWxMibModule.contactinfo: Customer Support Juniper Networks, Inc. 1194 North Mathilda Avenue Sunnyvale, CA 94089 +1 888-314-JTAC support@juniper.net
jnxWxMibModule.description: A MIB module containing definitions of managed objects for Juniper Networks' WAN Acceleration family of products.

jnxWxConfMib.name: jnxWxConfMib
jnxWxConfMib.description: Sub-tree for WAN Acceleration MIB conformance statements.

jnxWxObjs.name: jnxWxObjs

jnxWxStatsUpdateTime.name: jnxWxStatsUpdateTime
jnxWxStatsUpdateTime.description: This is the value of sysUpTime when the WX stats (jnxWxSysStats, jnxWxAsm, jnxWxApp) were last updated. The management station can use this information to tell if it's downloading a consistent set of stats.

jnxWxStatsAsmCount.name: jnxWxStatsAsmCount
jnxWxStatsAsmCount.description: The number of Decompressors this Compressor has had a session with at any time during the last two months.

jnxWxStatsVirtEndptCount.name: jnxWxStatsVirtEndptCount
jnxWxStatsVirtEndptCount.description: The number of virtual endpoints configured on this WX

jnxWxStatsAppCount.name: jnxWxStatsAppCount
jnxWxStatsAppCount.description: The number of applications currently being monitored on this Compressor.

jnxWxStatsAccelAppCount.name: jnxWxStatsAccelAppCount
jnxWxStatsAccelAppCount.description: The number of applications currently being accelerated on this Compressor.

jnxWxStatsQosClassCount.name: jnxWxStatsQosClassCount
jnxWxStatsQosClassCount.description: The number of QoS classes currently being monitored on this Compressor.

jnxWxStatsQosEndptCount.name: jnxWxStatsQosEndptCount
jnxWxStatsQosEndptCount.description: The number of QoS endpoints currently being monitored on this Compressor.

jnxWxStatsWpEndptCount.name: jnxWxStatsWpEndptCount
jnxWxStatsWpEndptCount.description: Number of endpoints with WAN performance monitoring enabled

jnxWxSysStats.name: jnxWxSysStats
jnxWxSysStats.description: Sub-tree for WAN Acceleration system statistics.

jnxWxSysStatsBytesInAe.name: jnxWxSysStatsBytesInAe
jnxWxSysStatsBytesInAe.description: Total number of bytes that entered the WX Assembly Engine since the system was started.

jnxWxSysStatsBytesOutAe.name: jnxWxSysStatsBytesOutAe
jnxWxSysStatsBytesOutAe.description: Total number of bytes that exited the WX Assembly Engine after assembly since the system was started.

jnxWxSysStatsPktsInAe.name: jnxWxSysStatsPktsInAe
jnxWxSysStatsPktsInAe.description: Total number of packets that entered the WX Assembly Engine since the system was started.

jnxWxSysStatsPktsOutAe.name: jnxWxSysStatsPktsOutAe
jnxWxSysStatsPktsOutAe.description: Total number of packets that exited the WX Assembly Engine after assembly since the system was started.

jnxWxSysStatsBytesOutOob.name: jnxWxSysStatsBytesOutOob
jnxWxSysStatsBytesOutOob.description: Total number of out-of-band bytes sent to the control channel since the system was started.

jnxWxSysStatsBytesPtNoAe.name: jnxWxSysStatsBytesPtNoAe
jnxWxSysStatsBytesPtNoAe.description: Total number of bytes that passed through the WX Compression Engine because there was no corresponding Assembly Engine WX, since the system was started.

jnxWxSysStatsPktsPtNoAe.name: jnxWxSysStatsPktsPtNoAe
jnxWxSysStatsPktsPtNoAe.description: Total number of packets that passed through the WX Compression Engine because there was no corresponding Assembly Engine WX, since the system was started.

jnxWxSysStatsBytesPtFilter.name: jnxWxSysStatsBytesPtFilter
jnxWxSysStatsBytesPtFilter.description: Total number of bytes that passed through the WX Compression Engine due to a manually configured filter (such as an application filter), since the system was started.

jnxWxSysStatsPktsPtFilter.name: jnxWxSysStatsPktsPtFilter
jnxWxSysStatsPktsPtFilter.description: Total number of packets that passed through the WX Compression Engine due to a manually configured filter (such as an application filter), since the system was started.

jnxWxSysStatsBytesOfPt.name: jnxWxSysStatsBytesOfPt
jnxWxSysStatsBytesOfPt.description: Total number of bytes that passed through the WX Compression Engine due to device buffer overflow, since the system was started.

jnxWxSysStatsPktsOfPt.name: jnxWxSysStatsPktsOfPt
jnxWxSysStatsPktsOfPt.description: Total number of packets that passed through the WX Compression Engine due to device buffer overflow, since the system was started.

jnxWxSysStatsBytesTpIn.name: jnxWxSysStatsBytesTpIn
jnxWxSysStatsBytesTpIn.description: The number of bytes into the WX Compression Engine at the peak five-second interval of data input, since the system was started.

jnxWxSysStatsPktsTpIn.name: jnxWxSysStatsPktsTpIn
jnxWxSysStatsPktsTpIn.description: The number of packets into the WX Compression Engine at the peak five-second interval of data input, since the system was started.

jnxWxSysStatsBytesTpOut.name: jnxWxSysStatsBytesTpOut
jnxWxSysStatsBytesTpOut.description: The number of bytes out of the WX Compression Engine at the peak five-second interval of data input, since the system was started.

jnxWxSysStatsPktsTpOut.name: jnxWxSysStatsPktsTpOut
jnxWxSysStatsPktsTpOut.description: The number of packets out of the WX Compression Engine at the peak five-second interval of data input, since the system was started.

jnxWxSysStatsBytesTpPt.name: jnxWxSysStatsBytesTpPt
jnxWxSysStatsBytesTpPt.description: The number of bytes that passed through the WX Compression Engine at the peak five-second interval of data input, since the system was started.

jnxWxSysStatsPktsTpPt.name: jnxWxSysStatsPktsTpPt
jnxWxSysStatsPktsTpPt.description: The number of packets that passed through the WX Compression Engine at the peak five-second interval of data input, since the system was started.

jnxWxSysStatsPeakRdn.name: jnxWxSysStatsPeakRdn
jnxWxSysStatsPeakRdn.description: The maximum data reduction rate for a five second interval in the last minute. The value returned is (percentage * 1000). Applications should divide the returned value by 1000.

jnxWxSysStatsThruputIn.name: jnxWxSysStatsThruputIn
jnxWxSysStatsThruputIn.description: Average throughput of incoming data in Kbps since the system was started.

jnxWxSysStatsThruputOut.name: jnxWxSysStatsThruputOut
jnxWxSysStatsThruputOut.description: Average throughput of outgoing data in Kbps since the system was started.

jnxWxSysStatsBytesInRe.name: jnxWxSysStatsBytesInRe
jnxWxSysStatsBytesInRe.description: Total number of bytes that entered the WX Compression Engine since the system was started.

jnxWxSysStatsBytesOutRe.name: jnxWxSysStatsBytesOutRe
jnxWxSysStatsBytesOutRe.description: Total number of bytes that exited the WX Compression Engine after reduction since the system was started.

jnxWxSysStatsPktsInRe.name: jnxWxSysStatsPktsInRe
jnxWxSysStatsPktsInRe.description: Total number of packets that entered the WX Compression Engine since the system was started.

jnxWxSysStatsPktsOutRe.name: jnxWxSysStatsPktsOutRe
jnxWxSysStatsPktsOutRe.description: Total number of packets that exited the WX Compression Engine after reduction since the system was started.

jnxWxAsm.name: jnxWxAsm
jnxWxAsm.description: Information maintained by a Compressor for each Decompressor it has a session with.

jnxWxAsmTable.name: jnxWxAsmTable
jnxWxAsmTable.description: List of Decompressors the Compressor has sessions with.

jnxWxAsmIpAddress.name: jnxWxAsmIpAddress
jnxWxAsmIpAddress.description: The IP address of the Decompressor.

jnxWxAsmStatsTable.name: jnxWxAsmStatsTable
jnxWxAsmStatsTable.description: Statistics maintained by a Compressor for each Decompressor it has a session with.

jnxWxAsmStatsPktsIn.name: jnxWxAsmStatsPktsIn
jnxWxAsmStatsPktsIn.description: The total number of packets into this WX, since the system was started, that were identified for reduction and addressed to the WX whose IP address is in the row in jnxWxAsmTable that matches this row.

jnxWxAsmStatsPktsOut.name: jnxWxAsmStatsPktsOut
jnxWxAsmStatsPktsOut.description: The total number of packets out of this WX, since the system was started, that were identified for reduction and addressed to the WX whose IP address is in the row in jnxWxAsmTable that matches this row.

jnxWxAsmStatsBytesIn.name: jnxWxAsmStatsBytesIn
jnxWxAsmStatsBytesIn.description: The total number of bytes into this WX, since the system was started, that were identified for reduction and addressed to the WX whose IP address is in the row in jnxWxAsmTable that matches this row.

jnxWxAsmStatsBytesOut.name: jnxWxAsmStatsBytesOut
jnxWxAsmStatsBytesOut.description: The total number of bytes out of this WX, since the system was started, that were identified for reduction and addressed to the WX whose IP address is in the row in jnxWxAsmTable that matches this row.

jnxWxVirtEndptTable.name: jnxWxVirtEndptTable
jnxWxVirtEndptTable.description: Virtual Endpoints defined in this WX

jnxWxVirtEndptName.name: jnxWxVirtEndptName
jnxWxVirtEndptName.description: The name of the configured virtual endpoint

jnxWxVirtEndptSubnetCount.name: jnxWxVirtEndptSubnetCount
jnxWxVirtEndptSubnetCount.description: The number of subnets associated with this virtual endpoint

jnxWxApp.name: jnxWxApp
jnxWxApp.description: Information maintained by a Compressor for each application that is monitored.

jnxWxAppAppName.name: jnxWxAppAppName
jnxWxAppAppName.description: The name of the application from which the data was received (e.g., FTP, HTTP, Lotus Notes).

jnxWxAppStatsTable.name: jnxWxAppStatsTable
jnxWxAppStatsTable.description: Statistics maintained by a Compressor for each application that is monitored.

jnxWxAppStatsEntry.name: jnxWxAppStatsEntry
jnxWxAppStatsEntry.description: A row in jnxWxAppStatsTable. Note that the indices are from jnxWxAsmTable and jnxWxAppTable. For each Decompressor this compressor has a session with (indexed by jnxWxAsmIndex), statistics are maintained for each application that is monitored (indexed by jnxWxAppIndex).

jnxWxAppStatsBytesIn.name: jnxWxAppStatsBytesIn
jnxWxAppStatsBytesIn.description: The total number of bytes into the WX, since the system was started, that were identified for reduction, and addressed to the WX whose IP address is in the row in jnxWxAsmTable that matches the index jnxWxAsmIndex, and that was received from the application whose name is in the row in jnxWxAppTable that matches the index jnxWxAppIndex.

jnxWxAppStatsBytesOut.name: jnxWxAppStatsBytesOut
jnxWxAppStatsBytesOut.description: The total number of bytes out of the WX, since the system was started, that were identified for reduction, and addressed to the WX whose IP address is in the row in jnxWxAsmTable that matches the index jnxWxAsmIndex, and that was received from the application whose name is in the row in jnxWxAppTable.

jnxWxAppStatsBytesInPercent.name: jnxWxAppStatsBytesInPercent
jnxWxAppStatsBytesInPercent.description: The percentage of the bytes in for this application over the total bytes into the WX, since the system was started, that were identified for reduction, and addressed to the WX whose IP address is in the row in jnxWxAsmTable that matches the index jnxWxAsmIndex, and that was received from the application whose name is in the row in jnxWxAppTable that matches the index jnxWxAppIndex. The value returned is (percentage * 1000). Applications should divide the returned value by 1000.

jnxWxAppStatsAppName.name: jnxWxAppStatsAppName
jnxWxAppStatsAppName.description: The name of the application from which the data was received (e.g., FTP, HTTP, Lotus Notes). NOTE: This object is here even though it's also in jnxWxAppTable. This is for the convenience of network monitoring tools that require all columns to be from the same table.

jnxWxAppAggrStatsTable.name: jnxWxAppAggrStatsTable
jnxWxAppAggrStatsTable.description: Aggregate statistics maintained by a Compressor for each application that is monitored. These statistics apply to the compressor as a whole and are summed over all decompressor sessions maintained by the compressor.

jnxWxAppAggrStatsBytesInRe.name: jnxWxAppAggrStatsBytesInRe
jnxWxAppAggrStatsBytesInRe.description: Total number of bytes that entered the WX Compression Engine for this application since the system was started.

jnxWxAppAggrStatsBytesOutRe.name: jnxWxAppAggrStatsBytesOutRe
jnxWxAppAggrStatsBytesOutRe.description: Total number of bytes that exited the WX Compression Engine after reduction for this application since the system was started.

jnxWxAppAggrStatsBytesInPercent.name: jnxWxAppAggrStatsBytesInPercent
jnxWxAppAggrStatsBytesInPercent.description: The percentage of the bytes in for this application over the total bytes into the WX Compression Engine. The value returned is (percentage * 1000). Applications should divide the returned value by 1000.

jnxWxWanStatsEntry.name: jnxWxWanStatsEntry
jnxWxWanStatsEntry.description: A row in jnxWxWanStatsTable. Note that the indices are from jnxWxAsmTable and jnxWxAppTable. For each Decompressor this compressor has a session with (indexed by jnxWxAsmIndex), statistics are maintained for each application that is monitored (indexed by jnxWxAppIndex).

jnxWxWanStatsBytesToWan.name: jnxWxWanStatsBytesToWan
jnxWxWanStatsBytesToWan.description: Total number of bytes sent to the wan on a per application basis

jnxWxWanStatsBytesFromWan.name: jnxWxWanStatsBytesFromWan
jnxWxWanStatsBytesFromWan.description: Total number of bytes received from the WAN on a per application basis

jnxWxAccelAppNameTable.name: jnxWxAccelAppNameTable
jnxWxAccelAppNameTable.description: List of applications that can be accelerated by the WX device.

jnxWxAccelAppNameEntry.name: jnxWxAccelAppNameEntry
jnxWxAccelAppNameEntry.description: A row in jnxWxAccelAppNameTable. Each row contains the name of an application that can be accelerated.

jnxWxAccelAppName.name: jnxWxAccelAppName
jnxWxAccelAppName.description: The name of the application from which the data was received (e.g., FTP, HTTP, Lotus Notes).

jnxWxAccelAppStatsTable.name: jnxWxAccelAppStatsTable
jnxWxAccelAppStatsTable.description: Accelerated application performance statistics. Includes time with and without acceleration in seconds

jnxWxAccelAppStatsEntry.name: jnxWxAccelAppStatsEntry
jnxWxAccelAppStatsEntry.description: A row in jnxWxAccelAppStatsTable. Indices are from jnxWxAsmTable and jnxWxAccelAppNameTable. For each Decompressor this compressor has a session with (indexed by jnxWxAsmIndex), statistics are maintained for each application that is accelereated (indexed by jnxWxAccelAppIndex)

jnxWxAccelAppTimeWithAccel.name: jnxWxAccelAppTimeWithAccel
jnxWxAccelAppTimeWithAccel.description: Total number of seconds required to complete all transactions with acceleration enabled.

jnxWxAccelAppTimeWithoutAccel.name: jnxWxAccelAppTimeWithoutAccel
jnxWxAccelAppTimeWithoutAccel.description: Total number of seconds that would be required to complete all transactions if acceleration was disabled.

jnxWxBurstStats.name: jnxWxBurstStats
jnxWxBurstStats.description: Sub-tree for WAN Acceleration system statistics.

jnxWxBurstStatsStartTime.name: jnxWxBurstStatsStartTime
jnxWxBurstStatsStartTime.description: The start of the minute in seconds since midnight (00:00:00), January 1, 1970, UTC over which the burst stats apply.

jnxWxBurstStatsBpsIn.name: jnxWxBurstStatsBpsIn
jnxWxBurstStatsBpsIn.description: Burst bits per second into reduction engine for the past minute.

jnxWxBurstStatsBpsOut.name: jnxWxBurstStatsBpsOut
jnxWxBurstStatsBpsOut.description: Burst bits per second out of reduction engine for the past minute.

jnxWxBurstStatsBpsPt.name: jnxWxBurstStatsBpsPt
jnxWxBurstStatsBpsPt.description: Burst pass-through bits per second for the past minute.

jnxWxQos.name: jnxWxQos
jnxWxQos.description: Information maintained by a Compressor for each QoS class that is monitored.

jnxWxQosEndptTable.name: jnxWxQosEndptTable
jnxWxQosEndptTable.description: List of endpoints managed by QoS.

jnxWxQosEndptIdentifier.name: jnxWxQosEndptIdentifier
jnxWxQosEndptIdentifier.description: The IP address of an Decompressor or the name of a virtual endpoint.

jnxWxQosClassTable.name: jnxWxQosClassTable
jnxWxQosClassTable.description: List of QoS classes currently monitored.

jnxWxQosClassName.name: jnxWxQosClassName
jnxWxQosClassName.description: The name of the QoS class

jnxWxQosStatsEntry.name: jnxWxQosStatsEntry
jnxWxQosStatsEntry.description: A row in the jnxWxQosStatsTable. Indexed by decompressor and the corresponding QoS class. Statistics are maintained per endpoint (indexed by jnxWxQosEndptIndex) and per QoS class associated with the endpoint (indexed by jnxWxQosClassIndex)

jnxWxQosStatsBytesIn.name: jnxWxQosStatsBytesIn
jnxWxQosStatsBytesIn.description: Total number of bytes received from the WAN on a per class basis

jnxWxQosStatsBytesOut.name: jnxWxQosStatsBytesOut
jnxWxQosStatsBytesOut.description: Total number of bytes sent to the WAN on a per class basis

jnxWxQosStatsBytesDropped.name: jnxWxQosStatsBytesDropped
jnxWxQosStatsBytesDropped.description: Total number of bytes dropped on a per class basis

jnxWxQosStatsPktsIn.name: jnxWxQosStatsPktsIn
jnxWxQosStatsPktsIn.description: Total number of packets received from the WAN on a per class basis

jnxWxQosStatsPktsOut.name: jnxWxQosStatsPktsOut
jnxWxQosStatsPktsOut.description: Total number of packets sent to the wan on a per class basis

jnxWxQosStatsPktsDropped.name: jnxWxQosStatsPktsDropped
jnxWxQosStatsPktsDropped.description: Total number of packets dropped on a per class basis

jnxWxWpEndptTable.name: jnxWxWpEndptTable
jnxWxWpEndptTable.description: List of endpoints managed by Multi-path

jnxWxEventObjs.name: jnxWxEventObjs
jnxWxEventObjs.description: Branch for objects meant only to be sent in event varbinds.

jnxWxEventEventsV2.name: jnxWxEventEventsV2
jnxWxEventEventsV2.description: Branch for SNMPv2 events. The OIDs for SNMPv2 events should have a zero as the next-to-last sub-identifier (as specified in RFC1902).

jnxWxEventCompressionBufferOverflow.name: jnxWxEventCompressionBufferOverflow
jnxWxEventCompressionBufferOverflow.description: The compressor's input buffer is approaching full capacity. This trap is currently unused.

jnxWxEventCompressionSessionClosed.name: jnxWxEventCompressionSessionClosed
jnxWxEventCompressionSessionClosed.description: The compressor's session to the device described in jnxWxCommonEventDescr was terminated.

jnxWxEventDecompressionSessionClosed.name: jnxWxEventDecompressionSessionClosed
jnxWxEventDecompressionSessionClosed.description: The decompressor's session to the device described in jnxWxCommonEventDescr was terminated.

jnxWxEventCompressionSessionOpened.name: jnxWxEventCompressionSessionOpened
jnxWxEventCompressionSessionOpened.description: The compressor's session to the device described in jnxWxCommonEventDescr was opened.

jnxWxEventDecompressionSessionOpened.name: jnxWxEventDecompressionSessionOpened
jnxWxEventDecompressionSessionOpened.description: The decompressor's session to the device described in jnxWxCommonEventDescr was opened.

jnxWxEventPrimaryRegServerUnreachable.name: jnxWxEventPrimaryRegServerUnreachable
jnxWxEventPrimaryRegServerUnreachable.description: The primary registration server is currently unreachable.

jnxWxEventSecondaryRegServerUnreachable.name: jnxWxEventSecondaryRegServerUnreachable
jnxWxEventSecondaryRegServerUnreachable.description: The secondary registration server is currently unreachable.

jnxWxEventMultiNodeMasterUp.name: jnxWxEventMultiNodeMasterUp
jnxWxEventMultiNodeMasterUp.description: The system designated as the 'master' of a multi-node came up. This notification is generated by the system that's designated as the 'master' of the multi-node. Note that the corresponding Down notification is generated by the designated 'master-backup' of the same multi-node. This trap is currently unused.

jnxWxEventMultiNodeMasterDown.name: jnxWxEventMultiNodeMasterDown
jnxWxEventMultiNodeMasterDown.description: The system designated as the 'master' of a multi-node is currently down. This notification is generated by the system that's designated as the 'master-backup' of the same multi-node. Note that the corresponding Up notification is generated by the designated 'master' of the same multi-node. This trap is currently unused.

jnxWxEventMultiNodeLastUp.name: jnxWxEventMultiNodeLastUp
jnxWxEventMultiNodeLastUp.description: The system designated as the 'last-node' of a multi-node came up. This notification is generated by the system that's designated as the 'last-node' of the multi-node. Note that the corresponding Down notification is generated by the designated 'master' of the same multi-node. This trap is currently unused.

jnxWxEventMultiNodeLastDown.name: jnxWxEventMultiNodeLastDown
jnxWxEventMultiNodeLastDown.description: The system designated as the 'last-node' of a multi-node is currently down. This notification is generated by the system that's designated as the 'master' of the same multi-node. Note that the corresponding Up notification is generated by the designated 'last-node' of the same multi-node. This trap is currently unused.

jnxWxEventPrimaryDownBackupEngaged.name: jnxWxEventPrimaryDownBackupEngaged
jnxWxEventPrimaryDownBackupEngaged.description: The system designated as the 'primary' is currently unreachable. This notification is generated by the system that's designated as the 'backup' device. The backup device is engaged for the primary device.

jnxWxEventPrimaryDownBackupEngageFailed.name: jnxWxEventPrimaryDownBackupEngageFailed
jnxWxEventPrimaryDownBackupEngageFailed.description: The system designated as the 'primary' is currently unreachable. This notification is generated by the system that's designated as the 'backup' device. The backup device failed to engage for the primary device.

jnxWxEventPrimaryUpBackupDisengaged.name: jnxWxEventPrimaryUpBackupDisengaged
jnxWxEventPrimaryUpBackupDisengaged.description: The system designated as the 'primary' is currently reachable. This notification is generated by the system that's designated as the 'backup' device. The backup device has disengaged itself.

jnxWxEventMultiPathStatusChange.name: jnxWxEventMultiPathStatusChange
jnxWxEventMultiPathStatusChange.description: The status of the primary or secondary path to another multi-path enabled system changed. The path became inactive or failed after previously being active or vice versa. This might have caused traffic designated to flow over this path to be switched from or to this path.

jnxWxEventDiskFailure.name: jnxWxEventDiskFailure
jnxWxEventDiskFailure.description: A hard disk failed on the system. The system was rebooted, and will now operate without the downed disk, at a degraded performance. Dictionary accumulated until this point was lost.

jnxWxEventWanPerfStatusChange.name: jnxWxEventWanPerfStatusChange
jnxWxEventWanPerfStatusChange.description: The status of the Path on which WAN Performance Monitoring is enabled has changed. The performance of the path has changed either from acceptable to unacceptable or vice versa.

jnxWxEventDCQAboveHiWatermark.name: jnxWxEventDCQAboveHiWatermark
jnxWxEventDCQAboveHiWatermark.description: The decompression queue has reached the high watermark.

jnxWxEventDCQBelowHiWatermark.name: jnxWxEventDCQBelowHiWatermark
jnxWxEventDCQBelowHiWatermark.description: The decompression queue has fallen below the high watermark.

jnxWxEventPerformanceThreshCrossed.name: jnxWxEventPerformanceThreshCrossed
jnxWxEventPerformanceThreshCrossed.description: The threshold for a configured perfromance event has been crossed. This notification indicates that some system parameter being measured has reached a critical value.

jnxWxEventClientLinkDown.name: jnxWxEventClientLinkDown
jnxWxEventClientLinkDown.description: Link to the Client went down.

jnxWxEventClientLinkUp.name: jnxWxEventClientLinkUp
jnxWxEventClientLinkUp.description: Link to the client came up.
